x4freetext: It is o1506 and direct method
obtained reaction cross sections at other incident
energies.
The secondary beams were produced via fragmentation of
a 55 A*MeV Ca-48 primary beam on a 350-mg/cm**2 Ta
target.
Silicon detectors are used as active targets.
The high resolution magnetic spectrometer SPEG
installed at GANIL.
3-solid state silicon detectors, a 50-mum
delta-E, a 300-mum x-y position sensitive delta-E and
a 6700-mum E-detector. This silicon stack was
surrounded by a 4-pi array of 14 NaI(Tl) 13.1 cm
diameter and 23.5 cm long gamma-detectors.

x4freetext: *By authors*.With a set of two magnetic rigidity,
the nuclei of interest were separated and selected
with a small amount of light nuclei.
*By compiler*.Under "Reaction" is mean energy
integrated reaction cross-section.See Eq.(1) for
definition.
Since it is difficult to identify the quasi-inelastic
events from the elastic ones, some corrections on the
number of reaction events are necessary.
.The quoted errors correspond to the statistical
errors.
In text
S.B
